title: ITZY "SNEAKERS (English Ver.)" Lyric Video  @ITZY ​
textDisplay:
I don’t think they really needed to translate much. I get impression from how perfectly the rhyming couplets are that the song was probably written in English originally, then had bits translated into Korean for the main release.

The writers of the song aren’t Korean and it’s pretty common for songs to be written with a guide English lyric before being rewritten in Korean. If you lay out the lyrics of the Korean version there’s actually not much Korean in it lol

Itzy have done really well with their songs I think, in terms of having both Korean and English versions that work well without being clunky. They are, along with (G)I-dle, I think some of the best at it right now.

title: ITZY “SNEAKERS” M/V @ITZY
textDisplay: @Shiro I totally get where you're coming from. TBH, it takes some time to vibe with ITZY's songs. Like, when I first saw the music vid for their debut song DALLA DALLA, I was like, "Whoa, this is too much! The beat's all over the place!" But the more I listened to it, the more it grew on me and now I'm totally into it. Their sound is like if TWICE had a wilder, more rebellious little sis - and I'm a huge TWICE fan, so that's saying something! Anyway, after that, I started jamming to ITZY's other songs more and more.

title: ITZY “SNEAKERS” M/V @ITZY
textDisplay: @lshsmusiclover They are so catchy, it's impossible not to dance along! That's what I absolutely love about their music. I mean, seriously, who can resist bopping their head to "Wannabe" or jamming out to "#Twenty"? Those two are definitely my personal favorites! They just get me in the mood to sing and dance like nobody's watching!

But for Wannabe, Not Shy, Dalla, Loco and Mafia, Chesire, Boys like(idk) somehow unique. Would like to see a mature, edgy, dark, sexy, expensive, bossy concept. Itzy summer/bright/happy concept is so used from Dalla, Icy, Not shy, Sneaker then Cake. I usually see ITZY wearing sporty/gym clothes but here it's reallt different and I like the outfit here.

I hope all K-pop stars live their own life for their selves and not for some of these so-called fans. A true fan will be happy that they are happy. Like Itzy said I wanna be me.


Also, I hope Chen is not letting these crazy people get to him and I hope things get better for him and I hope he does not apologize anymore because he should not have apologized in the first place he had no reason to apologize to these crazy people. Also I had a hard time trying to find a bias but now I know it's Ryujin.
